[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":895},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F30\u002Fgit-filename-case-sensitivity-fix\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F30\u002Fgit-filename-case-sensitivity-fix\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F30\u002Fgit-filename-case-sensitivity-fix\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F30\u002Fgit-filename-case-sensitivity-fix\u002F":871,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F30\u002Fgit-filename-case-sensitivity-fix\u002F":880},"\u002Fgit\u002F20221230\u002F27133639\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":538,"date":855,"description":856,"extension":857,"lang":858,"meta":859,"navigation":201,"path":860,"readingMinutes":861,"seo":862,"standalone":863,"stem":864,"tags":865,"tldr":867,"updated":868,"url":869,"__hash__":870},"content\u002Fen\u002FGit\u002Fgit-filename-case-sensitivity-fix.md","Git Filename Case Sensitivity Issues and How to Fix Them","3639271727",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":846},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,68,71,121,124,131,134,150,157,222,237,241,244,249,264,267,281,288,309,332,341,373,381,386,402,407,534,540,550,563,567,583,586,604,615,620,700,710,810,822,828,832,842],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"A lot of people get burned by Git's case-insensitive filename behavior. So this post is dedicated to reproducing the issue and showing how to fix it.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"reproducing-the-issue","Reproducing the issue",[17,25,26],{},"Let's trigger this first so it actually sticks. Create a folder and a file:",[28,29,34],"pre",{"className":30,"code":31,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","mkdir test\ncd test\ntouch readme.md\n","bash","",[35,36,37,50,59],"code",{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,39,42,46],"span",{"class":40,"line":41},"line",1,[38,43,45],{"class":44},"smYoP","mkdir",[38,47,49],{"class":48},"sWayO"," test\n",[38,51,53,57],{"class":40,"line":52},2,[38,54,56],{"class":55},"stw71","cd",[38,58,49],{"class":48},[38,60,62,65],{"class":40,"line":61},3,[38,63,64],{"class":44},"touch",[38,66,67],{"class":48}," readme.md\n",[17,69,70],{},"Add it to Git and push to GitHub:",[28,72,74],{"className":30,"code":73,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"git init\ngit add .\ngit commit -m \"init\"\ngit push origin main\n",[35,75,76,84,94,107],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,77,78,81],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,79,80],{"class":44},"git",[38,82,83],{"class":48}," init\n",[38,85,86,88,91],{"class":40,"line":52},[38,87,80],{"class":44},[38,89,90],{"class":48}," add",[38,92,93],{"class":48}," .\n",[38,95,96,98,101,104],{"class":40,"line":61},[38,97,80],{"class":44},[38,99,100],{"class":48}," commit",[38,102,103],{"class":55}," -m",[38,105,106],{"class":48}," \"init\"\n",[38,108,110,112,115,118],{"class":40,"line":109},4,[38,111,80],{"class":44},[38,113,114],{"class":48}," push",[38,116,117],{"class":48}," origin",[38,119,120],{"class":48}," main\n",[17,122,123],{},"At this point your remote repo should look like:",[17,125,126],{},[127,128],"img",{"alt":129,"src":130},"GitHub","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FGoZjV4a.png",[17,132,133],{},"Now let's rename the file to README.md:",[28,135,137],{"className":30,"code":136,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"mv readme.md README.md\n",[35,138,139],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,140,141,144,147],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,142,143],{"class":44},"mv",[38,145,146],{"class":48}," readme.md",[38,148,149],{"class":48}," README.md\n",[17,151,152,153,156],{},"Run ",[35,154,155],{},"git status"," and you'll see:",[28,158,160],{"className":30,"code":159,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"On branch main\nYour branch is up to date with 'origin\u002Fmain'.\n\nnothing to commit, working tree clean\n",[35,161,162,172,197,203],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,163,164,167,170],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,165,166],{"class":44},"On",[38,168,169],{"class":48}," branch",[38,171,120],{"class":48},[38,173,174,177,179,182,185,188,191,194],{"class":40,"line":52},[38,175,176],{"class":44},"Your",[38,178,169],{"class":48},[38,180,181],{"class":48}," is",[38,183,184],{"class":48}," up",[38,186,187],{"class":48}," to",[38,189,190],{"class":48}," date",[38,192,193],{"class":48}," with",[38,195,196],{"class":48}," 'origin\u002Fmain'.\n",[38,198,199],{"class":40,"line":61},[38,200,202],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":201},true,"\n",[38,204,205,208,210,213,216,219],{"class":40,"line":109},[38,206,207],{"class":44},"nothing",[38,209,187],{"class":48},[38,211,212],{"class":48}," commit,",[38,214,215],{"class":48}," working",[38,217,218],{"class":48}," tree",[38,220,221],{"class":48}," clean\n",[17,223,224,225,228,229,232,233,236],{},"Now try ",[35,226,227],{},"git add ."," — and Git doesn't react at all. Why? Because by default Git treats ",[35,230,231],{},"readme.md"," and ",[35,234,235],{},"README.md"," as the same file, so it sees no change.",[12,238,240],{"id":239},"how-to-fix-it","How to fix it",[17,242,243],{},"Two approaches. The first is a Git config tweak, the second is a Git command.",[245,246,248],"h3",{"id":247},"git-config","Git config",[17,250,251,252,255,256,259,260,263],{},"Git has a setting that controls case sensitivity for filenames: ",[35,253,254],{},"git config core.ignorecase",". Setting this to ",[35,257,258],{},"false"," makes Git treat differently-cased files as different files, so it'll properly detect changes. By default it's ",[35,261,262],{},"true"," (ignoring case).",[17,265,266],{},"Rename README.md back first:",[28,268,270],{"className":30,"code":269,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"mv README.md readme.md\n",[35,271,272],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,273,274,276,279],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,275,143],{"class":44},[38,277,278],{"class":48}," README.md",[38,280,67],{"class":48},[17,282,283,284,287],{},"Then set ",[35,285,286],{},"core.ignorecase"," to false:",[28,289,291],{"className":30,"code":290,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"git config --local core.ignorecase false\n",[35,292,293],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,294,295,297,300,303,306],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,296,80],{"class":44},[38,298,299],{"class":48}," config",[38,301,302],{"class":55}," --local",[38,304,305],{"class":48}," core.ignorecase",[38,307,308],{"class":55}," false\n",[310,311,314],"callout",{"title":312,"type":313},"Note","note",[17,315,316,317,320,321,324,325,327,328,331],{},"There's also a global version of this setting, but using it means setting up a global Git config file, and it affects every project where you run ",[35,318,319],{},"git init",". I'd just use local — that way it only affects the current project.\nAlso, if you set ",[35,322,323],{},"git config --local core.ignorecase false"," locally and push to the remote, the remote repo also picks up ",[35,326,323],{},", so when you ",[35,329,330],{},"git clone"," later you don't have to set it again.",[17,333,334,335,337,338,340],{},"A quick word on ",[35,336,262],{}," vs ",[35,339,258],{},":",[342,343,344,359],"ul",{},[345,346,347,349,350],"li",{},[35,348,262],{},": Git ignores case\n",[342,351,352],{},[345,353,354,232,356,358],{},[35,355,231],{},[35,357,235],{}," are the same file",[345,360,361,363,364],{},[35,362,258],{},": Git treats differently-cased filenames as different files\n",[342,365,366],{},[345,367,368,232,370,372],{},[35,369,231],{},[35,371,235],{}," are different files",[310,374,375],{"title":312,"type":313},[17,376,377,378,380],{},"Running ",[35,379,254],{}," (no value) shows the current project's setting.",[17,382,383,384,340],{},"Now rename the file. I'm using ",[35,385,143],{},[28,387,389],{"className":30,"code":388,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"mv -f readme.md README.md\n",[35,390,391],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,392,393,395,398,400],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,394,143],{"class":44},[38,396,397],{"class":55}," -f",[38,399,146],{"class":48},[38,401,149],{"class":48},[17,403,404,405,340],{},"Then ",[35,406,155],{},[28,408,410],{"className":30,"code":409,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"On branch main\nYour branch is up to date with 'origin\u002Fmain'.\n\nUntracked files:\n  (use \"git add \u003Cfile>...\" to include in what will be committed)\n        README.md\n\nnothing added to commit but untracked files present (use \"git add\" to track)\n",[35,411,412,420,438,442,450,486,492,497],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,413,414,416,418],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,415,166],{"class":44},[38,417,169],{"class":48},[38,419,120],{"class":48},[38,421,422,424,426,428,430,432,434,436],{"class":40,"line":52},[38,423,176],{"class":44},[38,425,169],{"class":48},[38,427,181],{"class":48},[38,429,184],{"class":48},[38,431,187],{"class":48},[38,433,190],{"class":48},[38,435,193],{"class":48},[38,437,196],{"class":48},[38,439,440],{"class":40,"line":61},[38,441,202],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":201},[38,443,444,447],{"class":40,"line":109},[38,445,446],{"class":44},"Untracked",[38,448,449],{"class":48}," files:\n",[38,451,453,457,460,463,465,468,471,474,477,480,483],{"class":40,"line":452},5,[38,454,456],{"class":455},"s8XSl","  (",[38,458,459],{"class":44},"use",[38,461,462],{"class":48}," \"git add \u003Cfile>...\"",[38,464,187],{"class":48},[38,466,467],{"class":48}," include",[38,469,470],{"class":48}," in",[38,472,473],{"class":48}," what",[38,475,476],{"class":48}," will",[38,478,479],{"class":48}," be",[38,481,482],{"class":48}," committed",[38,484,485],{"class":455},")\n",[38,487,489],{"class":40,"line":488},6,[38,490,491],{"class":44},"        README.md\n",[38,493,495],{"class":40,"line":494},7,[38,496,202],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":201},[38,498,500,502,505,507,509,512,515,518,521,524,527,529,532],{"class":40,"line":499},8,[38,501,207],{"class":44},[38,503,504],{"class":48}," added",[38,506,187],{"class":48},[38,508,100],{"class":48},[38,510,511],{"class":48}," but",[38,513,514],{"class":48}," untracked",[38,516,517],{"class":48}," files",[38,519,520],{"class":48}," present",[38,522,523],{"class":455}," (use ",[38,525,526],{"class":48},"\"git add\"",[38,528,187],{"class":48},[38,530,531],{"class":48}," track",[38,533,485],{"class":455},[17,535,536],{},[127,537],{"alt":538,"src":539},"Git","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FiAwhXj3.png",[17,541,542,543,545,546,549],{},"Now Git actually detects the change — so you can ",[35,544,227],{},", ",[35,547,548],{},"git commit",", etc.",[310,551,552],{"title":312,"type":313},[17,553,554,555,557,558,232,560,562],{},"You should set ",[35,556,286],{}," during project init — if you do it later, you have a high chance of running into edge cases like two files (",[35,559,235],{},[35,561,231],{},") showing up on the remote after a push. Set it at the start to avoid the gotchas.",[245,564,566],{"id":565},"use-gits-built-in-command","Use Git's built-in command",[17,568,569,570,573,574,578,579,582],{},"Git also has a built-in command for renaming: ",[35,571,572],{},"git mv",". It changes the filename and Git detects the change properly. This is the simplest path — and what I ",[575,576,577],"strong",{},"recommend",". Format: ",[35,580,581],{},"git mv \u003Cold name> \u003Cnew name>",".",[17,584,585],{},"So:",[28,587,589],{"className":30,"code":588,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"git mv -f readme.md README.md\n",[35,590,591],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,592,593,595,598,600,602],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,594,80],{"class":44},[38,596,597],{"class":48}," mv",[38,599,397],{"class":55},[38,601,146],{"class":48},[38,603,149],{"class":48},[310,605,606],{"title":312,"type":313},[17,607,608,610,611,614],{},[35,609,572],{}," works for moving and renaming files. ",[35,612,613],{},"-f"," means force.",[17,616,152,617,619],{},[35,618,155],{}," and you get:",[28,621,623],{"className":30,"code":622,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"On branch main\nYour branch is up to date with 'origin\u002Fmain'.\n\nChanges to be committed:\n  (use \"git restore --staged \u003Cfile>...\" to unstage)\n        renamed:    readme.md -> README.md\n",[35,624,625,633,651,655,667,683],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,626,627,629,631],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,628,166],{"class":44},[38,630,169],{"class":48},[38,632,120],{"class":48},[38,634,635,637,639,641,643,645,647,649],{"class":40,"line":52},[38,636,176],{"class":44},[38,638,169],{"class":48},[38,640,181],{"class":48},[38,642,184],{"class":48},[38,644,187],{"class":48},[38,646,190],{"class":48},[38,648,193],{"class":48},[38,650,196],{"class":48},[38,652,653],{"class":40,"line":61},[38,654,202],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":201},[38,656,657,660,662,664],{"class":40,"line":109},[38,658,659],{"class":44},"Changes",[38,661,187],{"class":48},[38,663,479],{"class":48},[38,665,666],{"class":48}," committed:\n",[38,668,669,671,673,676,678,681],{"class":40,"line":452},[38,670,456],{"class":455},[38,672,459],{"class":44},[38,674,675],{"class":48}," \"git restore --staged \u003Cfile>...\"",[38,677,187],{"class":48},[38,679,680],{"class":48}," unstage",[38,682,485],{"class":455},[38,684,685,688,691,694,698],{"class":40,"line":488},[38,686,687],{"class":44},"        renamed:",[38,689,690],{"class":48},"    readme.md",[38,692,693],{"class":455}," -",[38,695,697],{"class":696},"sOudu",">",[38,699,149],{"class":48},[17,701,702,703,706,707,709],{},"Notice the difference from before — this says ",[35,704,705],{},"renamed",", while the ",[35,708,143],{}," approach said:",[28,711,712],{"className":30,"code":409,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},[35,713,714,722,740,744,750,774,778,782],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,715,716,718,720],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,717,166],{"class":44},[38,719,169],{"class":48},[38,721,120],{"class":48},[38,723,724,726,728,730,732,734,736,738],{"class":40,"line":52},[38,725,176],{"class":44},[38,727,169],{"class":48},[38,729,181],{"class":48},[38,731,184],{"class":48},[38,733,187],{"class":48},[38,735,190],{"class":48},[38,737,193],{"class":48},[38,739,196],{"class":48},[38,741,742],{"class":40,"line":61},[38,743,202],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":201},[38,745,746,748],{"class":40,"line":109},[38,747,446],{"class":44},[38,749,449],{"class":48},[38,751,752,754,756,758,760,762,764,766,768,770,772],{"class":40,"line":452},[38,753,456],{"class":455},[38,755,459],{"class":44},[38,757,462],{"class":48},[38,759,187],{"class":48},[38,761,467],{"class":48},[38,763,470],{"class":48},[38,765,473],{"class":48},[38,767,476],{"class":48},[38,769,479],{"class":48},[38,771,482],{"class":48},[38,773,485],{"class":455},[38,775,776],{"class":40,"line":488},[38,777,491],{"class":44},[38,779,780],{"class":40,"line":494},[38,781,202],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":201},[38,783,784,786,788,790,792,794,796,798,800,802,804,806,808],{"class":40,"line":499},[38,785,207],{"class":44},[38,787,504],{"class":48},[38,789,187],{"class":48},[38,791,100],{"class":48},[38,793,511],{"class":48},[38,795,514],{"class":48},[38,797,517],{"class":48},[38,799,520],{"class":48},[38,801,523],{"class":455},[38,803,526],{"class":48},[38,805,187],{"class":48},[38,807,531],{"class":48},[38,809,485],{"class":455},[17,811,812,813,816,817,232,819,821],{},"That's a big difference. With ",[35,814,815],{},"Untracked files",", you're essentially creating a new file — which has a high chance of ending up with duplicate files on the remote (both ",[35,818,231],{},[35,820,235],{},").",[17,823,824,825,827],{},"So the Git command approach is the cleaner one. Whenever you need to rename a file, use ",[35,826,572],{}," — it's the safer bet.",[12,829,831],{"id":830},"wrap-up","Wrap-up",[17,833,834,835,837,838,841],{},"Funny enough — while writing this post I got bitten by this exact issue. I'm so used to using ",[35,836,143],{}," that I kept wondering why something looked off. Halfway through writing I realized I should've used ",[35,839,840],{},"git mv -f",". So this post doubled as a refresher for me.",[843,844,845],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .smYoP, html code.shiki .smYoP{--shiki-light:#6F42C1;--shiki-default:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#FFB757}html pre.shiki code .sWayO, html code.shiki .sWayO{--shiki-light:#032F62;--shiki-default:#032F